Q2)Bubble Sort: Sort the salaries using the bubble sort algorithm.
#include <stdio.h>
#include <conio.h>
void main()
{
    int salary[50], n, i, j, temp;
    clrscr(); // Clear screen (Turbo C specific)
     printf("Enter number of employees: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
     printf("Enter salaries of %d employees:\n", n);
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        printf("Salary %d: ", i + 1);
        scanf("%d", &salary[i]);
    }
 // Bubble Sort Logic
    for (i = 0; i < n - 1; i++)
    {
        for (j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++)
        {
            if (salary[j] > salary[j + 1])
            {
                temp = salary[j];
                salary[j] = salary[j + 1];
                salary[j + 1] = temp;
            }
        }
    }

    printf("\nSalaries in ascending order:\n");
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++)

    {
        printf("%d ", salary[i]);
    }
      printf("\n");
      getch(); // Wait for key press (Turbo C specific)
}

Algorithm for Bubble Sort (Simple & Easy)

1.Start
2.Read the number of employees â†’ n
3.Read the salaries of all n employees into an array
4.Repeat the following steps for i = 0 to n-2:
-For j = 0 to n-i-2:
-Compare salary at position j with salary at position j+1
-If salary[j] is greater than salary[j+1]:
-Swap the two values
5.After all loops finish, the array will be sorted in ascending order
6.Print the sorted salaries
7.Stop
